User Story: As a vendor, I want to view and manage all my product listings from a centralized dashboard so that I can easily track submission statuses, take necessary actions, and keep my offerings up to date.
Acceptance Criteria
1. Dashboard Overview
1.	The system shall display a dashboard header containing four summary cards:
o	Total Products
o	Total Interest
o	Total Listings
o	Avg. Rating
o	Each card shows label, count, and (if applicable) a small trend indicator.
2.	The system shall display the navigation tabs exactly as per UI:
o	Product Upload
o	Product Management
o	Interest Expressed
o	Listing (selected by default for this screen)
o	Reviews & Ratings
________________________________________
2. Product Listing Section - Header
3.	The system shall show a section titled "Product Listing" with a subheading describing:
“Track your product listing submissions and approval status.”
4.	The system shall show a subsection “Your Product Listings” with supporting text:
“Review the status of all your product submissions.”
________________________________________
3. Filters and Search
5.	The system shall provide listing status filter pills with counts:
o	All
o	Under Review
o	Approved
6.	When the vendor selects/deselects a status filter pill:
o	The listing results shall update instantly.
o	Multiple filters may be active simultaneously.
7.	The system shall provide a search bar labeled “Search by product name…”
o	Typing in the search bar shall filter products by name (supports partial match).
8.	The system shall provide a dropdown for category filtering (“All Categories”).
o	Selecting a category shall show only products belonging to that category.
9.	The system shall provide a sorting dropdown (“Newest First”).
o	Sorting options shall include at least:
• Newest First
• Oldest First
o	The selected option shall reorder the listings accordingly.
________________________________________
4. Product List Display
10.	Each product listing card shall display the following elements:
•	Product icon (as per category)
•	Product name
•	Category label
•	Submission date
•	Status indicator (color-coded)
11.	The system shall use color-coded left borders for cards:
•	Blue → Under Review / In Progress
•	Orange → Pending or Awaiting Documentation
•	Green → Approved
12.	Each card shall display a status label with text matching backend status:
•	Under Initial Review
•	Awaiting Technical Documentation Review
•	Approved
•	Other statuses as applicable
13.	Cards associated with “Official AT” must show the appropriate badge (e.g., “Official AT”).
14.	Clicking anywhere on a product card shall open the product details screen (out of scope for this story).
________________________________________
5. Status Icon & Error Indicators
15.	For cards with pending or error-like statuses, the system shall display the small orange alert icon as shown in the UI.
•	Tooltip or hover text (if implemented) must provide explanation.
________________________________________
6. UI Persistence & Interaction
16.	The system shall ensure that filter selections, search input, and sorting choices remain applied when navigating within the Listing page.
17.	Changing any filter, search input, or sorting:
•	Shall refresh results without page reload.
________________________________________
7. Approval Process Panel
18.	The bottom section of the screen shall display a static information panel titled “Approval Process Timeline” showing:
•	Standard product listing timeline (1–2 business days)
•	Official AT listing timeline (3–5 business days)
•	Notification note (“You’ll receive email notifications for status updates”)
19.	This panel shall remain fixed at the bottom of the listing results within the page layout.
________________________________________
8. Empty State Handling
20.	If filtered results produce zero listings:
•	The system shall show a clear empty state message (e.g., “No products found.”).
________________________________________
9. Role & Access
21.	Only authenticated vendor users shall access this dashboard screen.
AC10: UI and Accessibility
•	The page is responsive across desktop, tablet, and mobile devices.
•	All interface elements follow WCAG 2.1 AA standards for accessibility.
•	Proper alt text, focus indicators, and ARIA labels are implemented.
AC11: Performance and Reliability
•	The page loads key content within 3 seconds under normal conditions.
•	Clear messages appear in case of downtime or data retrieval errors.
•	PWD sessions auto-timeout after a defined inactivity period (e.g., 30 minutes).
 

